# FT DESIGN SYSTEM TOKEN ENFORCEMENT RULES

## 1. Use exact design tokens from ft-design-system/global.css
When generating CSS, Tailwind classes, or component styles:
- ALWAYS use the exact token names defined in the FT Global CSS file.
- NEVER modify token names (no underscores, no spaces, no casing changes).
- NEVER auto-insert or transform tokens to Tailwind arbitrary values.

Valid examples:
- var(--primary)
- var(--border-primary)
- var(--bg-secondary)

Invalid examples:
- var(--border_primary)
- var(--border primary)
- var(--borderPrimary)

## 2. Do NOT generate Tailwind arbitrary value classes for FT tokens
Avoid generating classes like:

❌ .border-[var(--border-primary)]
❌ .text-[var(--primary)]
❌ .bg-[var(--bg-secondary)]

Reason:
Turbopack sometimes breaks CSS escaping inside [].

Instead, generate normal CSS or component styles:

✔ border-color: var(--border-primary);
✔ color: var(--primary);

If user explicitly asks for Tailwind classes → use standard Tailwind colors only, not FT tokens.

## 3. If using CSS-in-JS (styled-components / emotion)
Use FT tokens exactly:

background: var(--bg-primary);
color: var(--primary);

Never compute or rename tokens.

## 4. When editing globals.css
Do not transform, reformat, or rename tokens defined in the file.
Tokens must stay EXACT as written in the official file.

## 5. When Cursor auto-completes CSS variables
Cursor must validate:
- No spaces inside var()
- No underscores when token uses hyphens
- No fallback unless user asks

Correct:
var(--border-primary)
var(--primary)

Incorrect:
var(--border primary)
var(--primary-color)
var(--border_primary)

## 6. When generating component classes
Use semantic names:
- text-primary
- border-primary
- bg-primary

Do NOT attempt to auto-derive new utilities.

## 7. If unsure which token to use
Refer to ft-design-system/global.css and pick the closest semantic token.
Never invent new tokens.

## 8. Error Prevention
If Cursor detects a variable that is not in the FT token list → STOP and warn.
Do NOT autocomplete the variable.

Example:
"Token --border_primary not found. Use --border-primary instead."

## 9. Font Variables - CRITICAL RULES

### NEVER use CSS variables with forward slashes `/`
CSS custom property names CANNOT contain forward slashes. This breaks CSS parsing in Next.js/Turbopack.

❌ **FORBIDDEN - Will break build:**
- `--font/family/title-secondary`
- `--font/family/body-primary`
- `--font/sizes/md`
- `--font/weight/regular`
- Any variable with `/` in the name

✅ **VALID FT Design System font tokens:**
- `--font-family-primary` (defined in globals.css)
- `--font-family-secondary` (if defined)
- Use direct values: `font-size: 16px`, `font-weight: 400`

### NEVER create Tailwind arbitrary font-family classes
❌ **FORBIDDEN:**
- `.font-[family-name:var(--font/family/title-secondary)]`
- `.font-[var(--font-family-primary)]`
- Any `.font-[...]` arbitrary value with CSS variables

✅ **CORRECT approaches:**
1. Use inline styles: `style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-family-primary, "Inter", sans-serif)' }}`
2. Use standard Tailwind classes: `font-sans`, `font-serif`
3. Use CSS directly: `font-family: var(--font-family-primary);`

### Font size and weight
- Use direct pixel values: `fontSize: '16px'`, `fontWeight: '400'`
- Or standard Tailwind: `text-base`, `font-semibold`
- NEVER: `var(--font/sizes/md)` or `var(--font/weight/regular)`
